# 3. 夢いっぱいの結婚式

Minori: Sorry for the wait, everyone! The stream's back up and running♪
Comments: <There she is!> <Welcome back.>
Minori: Hehe. Thanks for waiting, you guys!
Minori: Guess what?! I've got some good news!
Comments: <Good news?> <Does it have to do with that girl you were talking to just now?>
Minori: Yeah, it actually does!
Minori: You're not gonna believe this! Today, we get to have one of the Phoenix Bridal Fair staff as our guide! Let's give Nene Kusanagi a big round of applause!
Nene: Oh... H-Hi...
Comments: <Oh, is this your friend?!> <She'll be on your stream?!>
Nene: U-Umm... Hello, viewers... My name is Nene Kusanagi...
Nene: Th-Thank you for having me on today...
Comments: <Your dress is so pretty!> <Welcome aboard!> <Wait, isn't she in WXS?!>
Minori: Hehe. That's right. She's a member of Wonderlands×Showtime! They put on the night show that went viral a little while back!
Minori: She's playing the lead in the wedding show that's taking place in the evening, so make sure to drop by the Phoenix Bridal Fair if you happen to be in the neighborhood!
Comments: <I wanna see the show!> <Does this mean you're gonna stream the show?>
Minori: Hehe. They all sound really excited! Thanks again for doing this, Nene!
Nene: R-Right. Of course...
Minori: Alright, now that we're all set and ready to go, it's time to resume Minori's walk through the Phoenix Bridal Fair...!
Nene: Alright, then... Let's start with the train wedding booth.
Minori: Oh, the train wedding...! That was in the pamphlet! It takes place on a real one, right?!
Minori: But how do you actually hold the ceremony...?
Nene: By renting out a part of a station. You hold the ceremony aboard a train car or on the tracks.
Nene: Apparently, the platform signs and line names are all specially designed for the wedding, so it's supposed to be a really memorable experience.
Minori: The platform signs...? Does that mean you can have the train headed for the “Paradise of Love” and stuff?! If so, that would be really memorable...!
Nene: I-I'm not sure about that...
Minori: Also, the wedding taking place on a train means...
Announcement: <The train carrying the bride will be arriving on this platform shortly. Please stand behind the yellow line for your own safety.>
Haruka: Thank you all for coming today!
Haruka: I hope you'll all give me a warm welcome when I arrive at the station of Eternal Happiness.
Minori: H-Harukaaa...!
Nene: Huh?! H-Hanasato?! Is something wrong?!
Minori: Th-The thought of Haruka being aboard that train almost made my heart explode...!
Nene: O-Oh, okay... You really surprised me there.
Comments: <That's our Minori for you.> <Always on the Haruka hype train.>
Nene: Everyone watching seems totally fine with this. I guess this is how she always is...
Minori: Hehe. Sorry, everyone. I really can't help myself...
Minori: But how amazing would it be to have the station announce that the bride is arriving on the platform?!
Minori: Everyone would toss flower petals into the air as she steps out of the train.
Minori: And she'd step back onto the train after its destination changes to the “Future”! Wouldn't that be so romantic?!
Nene: Your imagination's very specific...
Booth Attendant: I see... That certainly would be fun.
Nene: Huh?
Booth Attendant: Oh, pardon me. I'm in charge of this booth, and I gave what you just said a little thought...
Booth Attendant: The train displays and announcements can be changed easily enough, so your idea may be worth trying.
Minori: R-Really?! I'm glad to hear that what I said helped!
Nene: H-Her delusion ended up contributing...!
Comments: <Nice work!> <Way to go, Minori!>
Minori: Hehe. Thanks for the praise. But I have Haruka to thank for this...
Nene: I'm not sure how much credit Kiritani deserves...
Nene: But she seems happy enough. I guess it doesn't matter.
Minori: Anyway, next booth! Let's keep checking out as much as we can!
Nene: So, for the aquarium wedding, you rent out a part of it in order to hold the ceremony.
Nene: Like in the underwater tunnel. You can even have the dolphins jump out of the water when the bride and groom appear together. There really are a lot of fun options to choose from...
Minori: Wow...! This picture of the underwater tunnel's so pretty!
Minori: Just look at how the water's sparkling... This looks like the perfect place for someone like Shizuku to get married!
Comments: <Shizuku under the sea?!> <She'd be like a mermaid or undine...> <I'd love to see that! Even if it means my eyes melting away!>
Minori: You guys get it! Oh, I know! I should try to see if I can do a stream with Shizuku at the aquarium...!
Nene: Next, we have the great outdoors. You can hold weddings at campground and forest spaces that you've rented out.
Nene: You get to pitch tents, have a big barbeque and enjoy the things that only the natural world has to offer.
Minori: A big barbeque...! That'd suit Airi so well!
Nene: R-Really?
Minori: Yeah! I don't know how, but she's able to roast any type of meat just right!
Minori: Then, after the sun's gone down, and everyone's had their stomachs filled...
Minori: Airi would appear while holding a candle, and thank everyone for coming to her wedding, while blushing a little...!
Nene: Oh... That would be pretty nice.
Comments: <No! You're making me tear up!> <Congratulations, Airi.> <I wanna watch over Airi forever as one of the cedar trees!>
Minori: See what I mean?! Does this mean I have some natural talent as a wedding planner...?!
Comments: <No, an actual planner would need to be able to keep it together.> <You'd end up crying more than the families involved.>
Minori: N-No, that's not true!!!
Nene: (Hanasato really seems to be enjoying herself...)
Nene: (Not only that...)
Comments: <I didn't know weddings came in so many shapes and sizes.> <The Bridal Fair looks really fun!> <I wanna go too!>
Nene: (Her viewers also seem to be interested in the fair itself.)
Nene: (I really wasn't sure about this at first, but I'm glad I decided to help...)
Luka: (Hehe...)
Luka: (Nene seems to be enjoying herself very much♪)
Luka: (Talking about these wonderful wedding ideas seems to have eased her anxiety... And I like how... Mhm...)
Luka: (Zzz... Zzz...♪ I can probably sleep like a baby right now...)
Nene: Anyway, where should we go next?
Minori: I dunno. Every area looks like a lot of fun... No, wait!
Minori: I've got it! We should totally go here next!
